content.description: Climb the crack and groove on the west face of the boulder. Some of the rock might be friable, and there are tricky moves in a bad fall zone.
content.protection: Be careful- this has a rocky and sloped landing.
content.location:
If you are facing "

Huecos

," this is the crack/groove line to the right. Start about 6 feet lower than "

Huecos

".

content.description: Begin as low as you want, even sit start, on the west face, northern end. A few moves through pleasant huecos leads you to utilize a few disconcerting flakey crimps, and surmount a decent ledge. Finish straight up another 8 feet through a hueco and hard to see holds, or follow the ledge, traversing to the right (south) 10 feet for a fun alternate finish, meeting up with the topout of "West Crack".
content.location: Begin on the west side, northern end, on top of a small boulder resting on the ground.
